de.pifpafpuf.web.urlparam

Class UrlParamCodec<TYPE>

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.pifpafpuf.web.urlparam.UrlParamCodec<TYPE>
  • Type Parameters:
    TYPE - is the type of the parameter stored.

    public class UrlParamCodec<TYPE>
extends Object

    decodes and encodes parameter values of type TYPE from URLs and for HTML forms and links.

    Objects of this class are immutable. They are used to fetch parameters from the ServletRequest as well as to write the parameter with its value into a URL or an HTML form element.

    • Constructor Detail

      • UrlParamCodec

        public UrlParamCodec(String name,
             ParamCodec<TYPE> codec)
        creates a url parameter codec for a parameter with the given name and type.
        Parameters:
        name - of the parameter as used in the URL. No check is made whether the name conforms to the syntax rules of URL parameter names and no encoding/decoding is performed for the name.
        codec - is the codec to decode strings retrieved from ServletRequest and to encode the value for a URL or an HTML form input element. The codec should only encode/decode to/from an arbitrary String URL en/decoding is taken care of by this.

      • fromAll

        public List<TYPE> fromAll(javax.servlet.ServletRequest req)

        creates a list of TYPE objects from all values returned by req.getParameterValues() by calling fromString(java.lang.String, TYPE) for each of them. If the request parameter does not exist or ServletRequest.getParameterValues returns an empty array (no idea whether this may happen at all), a list of length zero is returned. If an individual parameter value cannot be parsed, it is skipped.

        Parameters:
        req - where to get the parameter values from, may not be null
